org.apache.river.test.spec.lookupservice.test_set01

Class EmptyLookup

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.river.qa.harness.QATestEnvironment
      • org.apache.river.test.spec.lookupservice.QATestRegistrar
        • org.apache.river.test.spec.lookupservice.test_set01.EmptyLookup
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Test, TestEnvironment

    public class EmptyLookup
extends QATestRegistrar
    This class is used to verify that when a lookup is performed using an "empty" template (a template created with all entries null) and ZERO maximum matches requested, the total number of service items registered in the Lookup Service will be returned; including the Registrar Service itself.
    See Also:
    TestEnvironment, QATestRegistrar, QATestUtils

      • construct

        public Test construct(QAConfig sysConfig)
               throws Exception
        Performs actions necessary to prepare for execution of the current QA test. Creates the lookup service. Creates all the service items. Registers all service items -- requesting ANY service ID. Creates a template with all entries null, that will be used in a lookup; and that will return all items registered.
        Specified by:
        construct in interface TestEnvironment

      • run

        public void run()
         throws Exception
        Executes the current QA test. Performs a match lookup using the template created during construct and zero maximum matches. Verifies that the expected number of services are returned by the call to lookup().
        Throws:
        Exception - if the test fails for any reason
